---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Case Studies — Datris.ai" description="See how leading financial institutions use Datris to centralize data, build enterprise data lakes, and accelerate AI/ML initiatives.">
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="bg-grid"></div>
      <div class="bg-glow" style="top: -200px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); background: var(--accent);"></div>
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section-label">Case Studies</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">Proven at <span class="gradient-text">enterprise scale</span></h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          From pension funds managing $200B+ to government-sponsored enterprises processing millions of records — 
          our platform handles the data challenges that matter.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <!-- Case Study 1: Pension Fund -->
    <section class="cs-detail">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cs-header">
          <div class="cs-badge-row">
            <span class="badge">Financial Services</span>
            <span class="badge">Data Lake</span>
            <span class="badge">AWS</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Enterprise Data Lake & Pipeline<br /><span class="gradient-text">$200B+ Pension Fund</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-grid">
          <div class="cs-main">
            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Challenge</h3>
              <p>
                This large pension fund managed over $200 billion USD across public equities, private equities, 
                real estate, infrastructure, and fixed income. Their data strategy had evolved organically — 
                individual teams built local solutions, resulting in a fragmented landscape of siloed data ponds 
                with no enterprise-wide visibility.
              </p>
              <p>
                Investment departments and core services groups needed timely access to all existing data, 
                the ability to introduce new datasets with ease, and a governance model that supported 
                cross-fund data sharing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Solution</h3>
              <p>
                We designed and built a cloud-based data ecosystem on AWS — a comprehensive data lake and 
                pipeline that became the central nervous system for data across the fund.
              </p>
              <div class="cs-solution-grid">
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">🏗️</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Cloud Infrastructure</strong>
                    <p>Project-based AWS account structure with Transit VPC networking, secure VPC endpoints, 
                    and infrastructure-as-code (Terraform) for repeatable deployments.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">⚡</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Data Pipeline (ETL)</strong>
                    <p>Automated sourcing, processing, and entitlement of data. Standard suite of tools 
                    enabling rapid onboarding of new data sources with simultaneous multi-source processing.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">🗄️</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Enterprise Data Lake</strong>
                    <p>Centralized repository for structured and unstructured data at any scale. 
                    Store as-is, then run dashboards, big data processing, real-time analytics, and ML.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">📖</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Data Catalog & API</strong>
                    <p>Searchable glossary of all available data with source definitions and entitlements. 
                    RESTful API enabling both application integration and analyst self-service.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">🔒</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Security Backbone</strong>
                    <p>Centralized security monitoring, identity and access management, and audit/compliance 
                    monitoring. All traffic stays within the cloud network — no public IPs required.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="cs-solution-item">
                  <div class="cs-solution-icon">🧪</div>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Sandbox Environment</strong>
                    <p>Dedicated experimentation zone with full data lake functionality for introducing 
                    new datasets and technologies without impacting production.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Impact</h3>
              <p>
                Investment groups across the fund can now discover, access, and perform analytics on 
                hundreds of datasets through the data catalog. Analysts access data directly via API into 
                their environments or leverage scalable cloud analytics (Spark) for intensive algorithms 
                across multiple datasets.
              </p>
              <p>
                The CI/CD pipeline reduced software delivery from months to hours. End-user involvement 
                during continuous development led to rapid feature iteration and usability improvements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-sidebar">
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">$200B+</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Assets Under Management</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">100s</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Datasets Catalogued</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">Months → Hours</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Deployment Time Reduction</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-tech-card card">
              <h4>Technology Stack</h4>
              <div class="cs-tech-tags">
                <span class="highlight-tag">AWS</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">S3</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Lambda</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Transit VPC</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Terraform</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Spark</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">CI/CD</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Data Catalog</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <!-- Case Study 2: GSE -->
    <section class="cs-detail">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cs-header">
          <div class="cs-badge-row">
            <span class="badge">Government</span>
            <span class="badge">Data Migration</span>
            <span class="badge">AWS</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Cloud Data Centralization<br /><span class="gradient-text">Government-Sponsored Enterprise</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-grid">
          <div class="cs-main">
            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Challenge</h3>
              <p>
                This large government-sponsored enterprise held vast amounts of mortgage, investment, and 
                personal data across numerous data warehouses and Hadoop environments. The firm maintained 
                40-50 people across distinct teams — each with replicated skill sets — responsible for 
                managing individual data environments.
              </p>
              <p>
                The legacy infrastructure was expensive, fragmented, and made enterprise-wide data 
                utilization nearly impossible.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Solution</h3>
              <p>
                We deployed the Datris Data Pipeline to centralize all data within AWS S3, while 
                integrating modern cloud technologies including Snowflake and MongoDB. The pipeline 
                automated the migration from legacy data warehouses to cloud-native object storage — 
                dramatically reducing infrastructure costs while enabling organization-wide data access.
              </p>
              <p>
                By leveraging S3 object-store technology at a fraction of the cost of traditional data 
                warehousing, the firm reallocated skilled employees from maintenance roles to 
                higher-value tasks.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="cs-section">
              <h3>The Impact</h3>
              <p>
                Now in its fourth year of implementation, this multi-year strategic initiative has 
                delivered strong, measurable results: reduced infrastructure costs, unified data access 
                across the enterprise, and accelerated the path to AI/ML-driven analytics.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-sidebar">
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">40-50</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Team Members Reallocated</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">4 Years</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Ongoing Engagement</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-stat-card card">
              <div class="cs-stat-value">~90%</div>
              <div class="cs-stat-label">Storage Cost Reduction</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-tech-card card">
              <h4>Technology Stack</h4>
              <div class="cs-tech-tags">
                <span class="highlight-tag">AWS S3</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Snowflake</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">MongoDB</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Hadoop Migration</span>
                <span class="highlight-tag">Data Pipeline</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="cs-cta">
      <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
        <h2 class="section-title">Your data pipeline <span class="gradient-text">starts here</span></h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin: 0 auto 32px;">
          Open source. Self-hosted. Battle-tested at the world's largest financial institutions.
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="https://github.com/datris/datris-platform-oss" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.013 8.013 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"/></svg>
            Get Started on GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="/about" class="btn btn-secondary">Meet the Team →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .cs-hero {
    padding: 160px 0 80px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .cs-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .cs-badge-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cs-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .cs-main {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  .cs-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .cs-section p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .cs-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cs-solution-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .cs-solution-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .cs-solution-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .cs-solution-item strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .cs-solution-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cs-sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 88px;
  }

  .cs-stat-card {
    padding: 24px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cs-stat-value {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: var(--gradient-text);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .cs-stat-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .cs-tech-card {
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .cs-tech-card h4 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .cs-tech-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .highlight-tag {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    background: rgba(0, 180, 255, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 180, 255, 0.15);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .cs-cta {
    padding: 100px 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-hero {
      padding: 120px 0 60px;
    }

    .cs-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cs-sidebar {
      position: static;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .cs-sidebar {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
